Text.Value: A little rest to brush the road from Boo's fur, and then back to our adventuring.
You come to speak of the last time Minsc stood watch? The snoring, it was Boo!
You will grow to like Jaheira's incense in time. Like - chewing herbs and soap, yes?
What is it, my friend?
Make sure you are refreshed before we set out again, friend. The road to justice is paved with kicked buttocks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Various pleasant greetings, exclusive to camp

Text.Value: *A whisper. The Absolute's voice, twisting the petty Guild thieves before you into snarling, savage beasts - feeding on the weak of your city.*
Do not be afraid, Boo! She is not here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Boo squeaks in alarm before the line
EditorData.SFXTags: [DS] Book squeaks at beginning of line

Text.Value: Everyone has the potential for good. It's just buried deeper in some, or lost along the way.
You are literally too dumb to be breathing.
On this matter, I have held small council with Boo. If the worm is lodged within our skulls, should it be not be possible to simply -
And in the end, it was she who died - protecting me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, but more bittersweet than grieving. It is what it is -he's made his peace

Text.Value: I suppose it has not caused you to paint the air with your innards of late.
I feel better. Minsc is ready to go and do some butt-kicking.
But still - I would hear what you have to say on the matter, my friend.
Bring forth the hydra, says Boo - more faces for the punching! First we pop the Zhentarim plot, then we show Nine-Fingers the five-fingers of Minsc. Yes?
Truly? But... you have seen my hamster, yes?
We need its power. The Emperor can help us control it, if we're careful.
I still do not understand.
Did the Emperor make you relive her death?
And that same one man... is Minsc.
A miniature giant space hamster.
You hear what our friend says, Boo? Viconia is gone for good this time!
- squeeeeze, like so -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Grits teeth and hunches over, growing red as he strains
EditorData.NodeContext: Hunches over and straining while clutching his fists. His face growing red.

Text.Value: I'm sorry. I didn't realise you were uncomfortable with our new power.
Which is why I am asking you.
Bah. Let me find a chance to demonstrate instead. It need not be a goblin - an unmannerly halfling will do. The point is this:
No.
True thoughts, meaning there are... untrue thoughts? As if someone would think one thing, but say another?
I see. In the case of Nine-Fingers, perhaps it was all bunched up in that finger she lost. It shall be for Minsc and Boo to be her virtuous pinky.
*It seems just the barest glimpse of what the man before you has seen and done: but enough to know that he has no right to still be alive.*
What.

EditorData.NodeContext: Flat, not interested in talking to us. We've brough his approval quite low.

Text.Value: Another Bhaalspawn, buried by our hand. Bhaal should learn better than to send his offspring against us - they might as well be babes, dropped bare-bottom into the Rashemen winter.
I'm just trying not to die. So please stop dipping your hamster in our food.
The parasite is evil - but with the Emperor's help, we can control its power.
Unless I die. Or you die. Or you do anything at all to upset Boo.
Eh... do you know, I think the feeling has passed. I am well. And it was just gas. And I have forgotten the question.
Ah, wait! That look in your eye - I know exactly what visions of Minsc you have seen, to cause you such wonder:
I'm a good listener.
What does it matter? Cultish thinking has occupied Minsc's mind for long enough - now it is time for doing.
I do not think our new friend wishes to see me blubbering, Boo.
Yes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

Text.Value: The Emperor has a way for us to become stronger. The Astral-Touched Tadpole.
There is a very ancient and very wise saying that Minsc lives by.
From what I saw, you took great pleasure in your work.
How was your reunion with Viconia?
I don't blame her - he is a scientific wonder.
I read it on the privy wall in the Blushing Mermaid many years ago.
Demonstrate. Reach out for his mind.
Why do we stop, my friend? There is evil somewhere with its small-pants yet unsoiled.
What? Minsc has the itch that only a butt can scratch! A kicked butt, I mean.
Stop wriggling, Boo, and prick up your ears.
Yes, my friend?
Leave.
That remains to be seen.
So you have no ideas for a cure?
Minsc shall be your shadow, as Boo is his.
Now - does Boo see a question in your eye, or just the parasite poking through?
No.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

Text.Value: We stand no chance if we don't use the tadpole's powers.
Go on. I'll meet up with you later.
Ohoho! This iciness, it will not withstand the forging fires of friendship. You will see!
I fear we cannot find our way to camp from here, friend. But we shall be so quiet, you will not even know we are here. Argh.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug - nothing you can do about it. 'Argh' is a loud and obnoxious yawn, immediately after promising to be quiet.

Text.Value: Please, my friend. Your noble tears will not make the confessing any easier.
Thrice-laced, in the Rashemaar style, so that a berserker might split skulls without fear of splitting britches, too.
If there is more we wish to know, we can simply... ask, no?
You are correct. I have no idea what any of that was about. But we shall simply - GAH!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc jerks in pain at end of line and goes fishing beneath his armour out of frame. Brings Boo out in cupped hands [same anim as recruitment]
EditorData.NodeContext: Minsc jerks in pain at end of line and goes fishing beneath his armour out of frame. Brings Boo out in cupped hands [same anim as recruitment]

Text.Value: You should stop listening to this Emperor. Minsc trusts it less than a Thayan Red Wizard.
Do you feel it, Boo? The path of virtue beneath my boots once more! Boo and I - we are in your debt, my friend.

EditorData.NodeContext: Begins eyes closed, just taking it in. Looks at player when addressing them.

Text.Value: Does it? You have seen all there is to see of Minsc, short of stripping me down to my stitches. Perhaps I can -
It is only justice, then, that we put a boot upon hers.
All the better, then!
Well... as have you, no? Do not forget that when you gaze into Minsc, Minsc also gazes into you.
But what does the parasite take in return? It is a horror, wrapped in honey - stay your sweet tooth, says Boo.
I see.
Hard to believe Shadowheart grew up in that place.
Boo is smart - sharing your emotions is a good thing.
Minsc does not trust it.
None at all. Though, Boo is tiny. Perhaps he could just crawl into our ears, and -

Text.Value: Minsc does not blame Minsc. Minsc blames the Stone Lord. But if the Stone Lord is Minsc, then, well... Minsc grows dizzy.
So I wonder. If Minsc can be a villain, and Nine-Fingers a hero: must it be so with all creatures? Is there good and evil within us all?
Minsc -
*Your face - the Stone Lord's face - mirrored in bloodied steel. In the heat of burning buildings, you hold your blade high above pale, frightened faces.*
She meant to spill his miniature guts and study them!
Hearing her voice again, for a moment Minsc almost believed it. But then the Emperor made a mistake - it did the one thing that Dynaheir would never, ever do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Rueful at how he was almost fooled - then amusement at how wrong the Emperor got it

Text.Value: If it cannot be Boo who pops inside my skull for a rummage, then I trust you.
Then you have a sword at your side and a hamster at hand, whenever you need them.
Evil might be turned to virtuous ends. Like hoisting a goblin by the toes so that you might use him to club another, larger goblin.
I do not pet him too - wait. You do what?

EditorData.NodeContext: Mid-objection before she realises the other half of what Minsc just said.

Text.Value: Thankfully, he preserved his guts heroically.
Oh? The mind of Minsc is a simple place. Of what strangeness do you speak?
I'm surprised you didn't kill her there and then.
No.
That would take the heart from even my hamster.

EditorData.NodeContext: After seeing something bad / sad: 'that was horrible'

There is good and evil in all! Let us go crack villainous skulls, so that the virtue might leak free!
Yes.

Why is he so scared of Viconia?
So I wonder. If Minsc can be a villain, and the Zhentarim now stand as the city's protectors - must it be so with all creatures? Is there good and evil within us all?
And you! Bite your tongue until your eyes water and your hairs curl!
In Baldur's Gate, they are likely to be rat-formed, and eager to charge rent. But Boo shall secure safe slumber for all!

EditorData.NodeContext: Boo squeaks in relief before the line
EditorData.SFXTags: [DS] Book squeaks at beginning of line

Why is Boo so afraid of her?

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

Text.Value: Discuss something else.
Speak of something else.

What happened to her?
A mouse?
What did she do to him?

Sorry - but why is he so afraid of her?
Say nothing.
Always.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

EditorData.NodeContext: Reluctant

EditorData.NodeContext: You've been dismissed but give a little look around - you don't know where camp is from here. You could be in a dangerous zone we can't camp in, a prison, or a literal dimension of hell. Either way, you're unfazed - just a little turned about.

Text.Value: What is it you want?

EditorData.NodeContext: Flat, annoyed, we've brought his approval a little low

Text.Value: If you cannot believe his words, then watch his doings! We will foil the Zhentish plot - and then we will show Nine-Fingers the five-fingers of Minsc! Yes?

No, Jaheira! The Zhent, the Guild - two cheeks of the same evil end. Minsc will punt them from the city, and with them all memory of this Stone Lord.

You're the worst bodyguard ever.
You're right. We should be wary of all mind flayers - Emperor included.
On this matter of sharing memories, I see no reason for us to worry at one another's worms.

More talk of tadpoles? The one of flesh and fish is not enough?
Never mind your pants. You've walked between planes, fought gods.
...Minsc will save his appetite for evil, I think.

Text.Value: The very mention of her name gives him nightmares to this day.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed aside - Boo is senstive about this,, it's a touchy topic

Text.Value: This could make all the difference in defeating the cult. Trust me, Minsc.

You must reach what Minsc cannot. The parasite - you can use it to tickle free whatever truth you seek.
Ah. Distressing.
Thank the gods you stopped her.

EditorData.stateContext: Boo out in Minsc's left hand.

Text.Value: I'm aware. You tried to kill me, multiple times.
She's gone now, Boo. You don't need to be afraid.
Now let us speak of something else.
I begin to wonder if good and evil is not a thing of knowing. If it is sometimes a thing that Minsc must decide for himself. Alone.
Ah... pay that noise no mind. Boo has not feasted on evil's flesh in some time, and it has set his gut to bubbling.
Perhaps.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

Text.Value: Ha! Minsc did not stop her - he did not need to.
That... is in the past. It showed me Dynaheir not as she was, but as she would have been. Should have been.
This Emperor played a very cruel trick - it made me believe that something lost had been found.

EditorData.stateContext: Boo in to Minsc's armour, not visible.

Text.Value: My friend, I promise you this - you have nothing to fear from Minsc.
*At first, there is nothing. His mind is empty as a still expanse of open country. But then:*
Viconia Viconia Viconia.
And she was right. The elders sent us out into the world, thinking it would teach her to bow a little.
But it was the world that bowed to Dynaheir, wherever she went, and Minsc blundered along behind.
More talk of tadpoles? Minsc crunched on the one of flesh and fish - was this not enough?
They are fiendishly complex, but fear not for Minsc. With training, he has learned to master the many little knots.
To camp, then. But if Boo grows restless and chews holes in all your delicates, you have only yourself to blame.

EditorData.NodeContext: tone of grudging acceptance

Text.Value: Shhht, friend. Boo does not like worms. They make his butt go itchy and take his mind from butt-kicking. We do not need these tadpoles...
As you wish - but quietly. It. Is. Listening.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Stage whisper, as if he can speak at a volume that deceives the parasite.

Text.Value: That was not Minsc. That was the Stone Lord.
Nine-Fingers did put a bounty on your head...
But no, Boo has only just made himself comfortable. Let us leave the inspection for camp.
Ohhh, this was the Lord Gortash we were sworn to do battle with, Boo?

EditorData.NodeContext: Reacting to Boo informing you the annoying man you just killed also happened to be one of the main villains in the game. Pleased grunt of surprise.

Text.Value: You'll hear no argument from Boo!
Kill the villains. Kill them all. Break them beneath my boots, no matter how they squeal for mercy.
Until Minsc arrives, the battle is not even begun.
Once again? In smaller words?
Argh!
Boo never sleeps deeply while evil is near. He sprang into action, and almost blinded the witch!
The brains to your brawn?
Minsc has made many mistakes, but he has learned from every one of them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Back to bravado.

Text.Value: Alas! Alack! It cannot be so!
It is not a matter of Minsc trusting you. It is his stomach that might prove treacherous. But...
Heh. Boo calls this nonsense. Less thinking of bad thoughts, says he, and more breaking of bad bones.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Reacting to an indignant Boo squeak.
EditorData.NodeContext: Reacting to an indignant Boo squeak.

Text.Value: *SQUEAK!*
And this talk of evil overthrowing evil - pah! Like a many-headed hydra biting at its own throat.
I see. I ask only because... this throwing of our lot in with the Zhentarim. I can see the good in it, if I stop and squint for a moment.
I don't need you right now. I'll meet you back at camp.
You say the path between good and evil is not always clear. Very well, says Minsc - Boo has always guided my boots, and so now he shall guide yours, too.
*Supportive squeaking.*
Dynaheir, hers was more the habit of teaching Minsc many new ways to say the word 'fool'.
Or I could just crack you over the head, see what shakes loose?
I much prefer your methods, my friend, but Boo is resolute. The worm it must be.
Huh. Pretty good idea.
Thank you, my friend. As ever, I shall do only what my heart and hamster tell me to:
Of course. Of course! One look into his beady little eyes should be enough to tell Minsc there is pure and untainted goodness in this world.
Your best friend?
Bah, I think on what she would say to Minsc now, cowering from a creature in his own skull. Fine! If you say this tadpole is a weapon, then let us wield it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Abrupt, snapping himself out of it. Grudgingly realising that Dynaheir would stop at nothing to end the Absolute, and so he can do no less

Text.Value: The only thing we have in common is the worm.
He who would try to control evil must beware lest evil tricks him, steals his clothes, and kicks his backside with his own boots.
When our minds mingled, I saw some... strange things.
Don't shy away from the tadpole. It's a useful way to know someone's true thoughts.
Ah. You are right, Boo. A ridiculous notion. It would be far too dark to see.

EditorData.NodeContext:
Nodding as Boo objects to the idea of being forced to crawl into our skulls and fish out the tadpole. Perhaps not getting the reason for Boo's objection entirely right.

Text.Value: Boo and Minsc have travelled far and wide, and met many fine and not-so-fine people.

Of course! But also -
Of course. A warrior speaks their mind, instead of reading others.
That is true, but he is also a living thing and has need of all his inner-parts.
If you have a problem following my judgement, now is the time to say it.
I did not get the chance!
Exactly so! If I must peer into the mind of my enemy, I use an axe. For friends, there is ale.
You believed you were following Jaheira - that's not evil.
A little butt-kicking before breakfast. No better way to start the day!
You can't blame yourself. The cult were manipulating you.
A moment, my friend. Minsc needs to think.

It's up to you.
No!
Let us speak later.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

You're doing it again - charging in without listening. Did you forget what Jaheira told you?
Is it power? True, it has made Minsc strong - Boo can scarcely get comfortable, so firm has my physique grown.
My pants.

Good. Boo will tell you when it is good that you talk again.

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral tone

*Your minds weave into one, what you seek laid instantly bare - his single innermost thought, at the very centre of his mind:*

No, my friend. If good and evil are a thing of the choosing, then it is for Boo alone to judge the virtues of his breakfast bath.
Ah, I spoke too soon of starting the day. I have told him he is pretty enough, but Boo insists on returning to the beauty sleep.

Text.Value: Trust me. This could make all the difference in defeating the cult.
Answer me honestly. What's with the hamster?
Minsc and Boo surely would, but you have so many followers already that Boo cannot pick your scent from the pack.
I do not often go against the advisings of my hamster, but... as you wish.
Maybe not. Let's talk about something else.
Even though it led to evil ends? And even the true Jaheira is not always right.
Dynaheir. A witch of my homeland. She was to be the greatest of them, and I her protector.
Or Jaheira - but she is currently possessed of an empty head.
It told Minsc exactly what he wanted to hear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Requesting slight re-take of this line with more warmth. He's remembering how the Emperor's attempted manipulations are exactly the opposite of the true Dynaheir's blunt and direct manner.

Text.Value: It may shock you both to know, but Minsc and this Stone Lord: they are one man. The same one man.
*The memories resurface, a lifetime of battles blurring into one. The single constant is Minsc, launching into the fray no matter the foe - be they god, monster, or man.*
Minsc is normally the strong and violent type, but if you insist on hearing a sad tale, he can tell it.
The drow was a cruel witch, but a clever one.
She knew what Boo was right away, and she had never seen his like before! She wished to inspect his handsome magnificence!
Oh, Minsc knows all about this Emperor. It has tried to introduce itself to me already.
It is not a matter of trusting you. It is... more a matter of trusting Minsc's stomach. But his steel and strength are still yours to command.
Sooner or later, it comes time to set the dizzy little demon down and do battle with him all the same. Do you understand my meaning?
It is simply that, the last time Minsc heaved great manly tears, Boo caught a nasty chill from the drowning.
Nine-Fingers Keene. That is what the Absolute bought black Zhentish steel to do - to kill the guildmaster!
I'd like to know a little more about you.

Synopsis: Minsc's default dialogue. In the current entries, he reflects on his opinion of us and our adventures so far, as well as revealing a little of history.
